        <argsstring>)(MLPowerManagerPowerState state, void *user_data)</argsstring>
        <name>on_power_state_changed</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This callback will be invoked when <ref refid="group___power_manager_1ga9ae517fbba90494f451bf38fcfac7a89" kindref="member">MLPowerManagerPowerState</ref> changes while a component is connected. If a component is disconnecting or is powering off, this callback does not get triggered. Instead, detecting a disconnected component can be done through the on_properties_changed callback. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">state</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><ref refid="group___power_manager_1ga9ae517fbba90494f451bf38fcfac7a89" kindref="member">MLPowerManagerPowerState</ref> representing the new power state. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">user_data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>User data as passed to the <ref refid="group___power_manager_1gafd4bc89d539a0de46b072fc8d2f06e98" kindref="member">MLPowerManagerSetCallbacks</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
